This is the sequence of screens for a typical TDE build, set up with the ./BUILD-TDE.sh script.

The most likely options at any stage have been set to default, so selection should mainly be pressing the Enter key.

Building the required packages

The Introduction appears once, before a build list has been created:

Selecting /opt/tde:


Selecting /opt/tde:


Selecting gcc:


Selecting <2> - editable for option <3>:


Selecting the default -j6, editable:


The Required packages don't include localization, which is in the tde-i18n package, so select default of none:


For a first run, building the Required packages, select the Stop option:


Select the default No - the build will stop at a failure and the build files for that package will be retained:


For this first run, select Yes:


Selecting Default:


Pre-selected Required packages, plus avahi-tqt selected if required for tdelibs


With tqt3 in the build list, this screen appears with selectable options:


With tdebase in the build list, this screen appears with selectable options - runlevel 4 chosen:

Build failure

Successful builds will be removed from the build list.
If, for example, tdeartwork fails, re-run the script with the Re-use option:


Decide whether to Continue or Stop at a failure - in this case, as there is only one package to be built, it doesn't matter:
